<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-808-558  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 808 558.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  Sept 3, 1990 v5 n110 p2(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>U.S. West: signs $25 million workstation contract with HP.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   U S West Inc. (contracts)Hewlett-Packard Co. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    HWP; USW.andO;Topic:     ContractsWorkstationsTelephone SystemsSupport Services.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>U.S.andP;  WEST:  SIGNS $25 MILLION WORKSTATION CONTRACT WITH HP.andM;Hewlett-Packard Co. has signed a $25 million contract to provide a network ofmore than 2,300 HP workstations and related peripheral products to US WESTfor use by telephone customer-service representatives.andM;US WEST plans to use the HP products to help its telephone-servicerepresentatives provide information to customers about billing and new orexisting phone services.andM;The HP workstation network is part of US WEST's implementation of itsDistributed Technology Platform, a long-range plan designed to distributecomputing power from mainframes to desktop systems.andP;  Under terms of theagreement, HP will supply US WEST with its products as part of the $25million first phase of the three-year contract.andM;The majority of the first-phase products will be HP 9000 Series 300 and 400workstations and servers.andP;  Both models are based on the Motorola 68030architecture and run the HP-UX operating system, which is based on and fullycomplies with ATandamp;T's UNIX system.andM;US WEST's first implementation of its Distributed Technology Platform is itsC-LINK application.andP;  The application will use HP's X client/server technologyin conjunction with the HP workstations to provide a consistent userinterface to customer- service representatives in regional customer-contactcenters.andM;Key Executives: Fred Ledbetter, director of Information Technologies Planningand Development for US WEST's Home and Personal Services Division.andM;Bill G. Kay, general manager of HP's Workstation Group.andO;</TEXT></DOC>